Scammers: A-holes just trying to run a con.
Spammers: Multiple listings for the same firearm.
Overpriced: Ridiculously high-priced items.
Best Offer: Those who think ARMSLIST is auction site, trying to get buyers into a bidding war.

To join the ARMSLIST Flagging Team contact us through this posting and include your first name and direct email address and we will add you to the team. We will send the posting’s URL out to all members of the flagging team and the ad will be removed! So if you want to help keep ARMSLIST a great place to deal firearms, join us today!

Cash or Postal Money order

http://s647.photobucket.com/user/Roanoker494/slideshow/Browning%20DA%2012ga

Here is a very nice Browning Double Auto "Twentyweight" 12ga 2.75" semi automatic shotgun built in 1955, this was the first year they were available in the USA. This shotgun was originally built with bird hunters in mind but I have found they are excellent shotguns for any small game or trap shooting, this has been my squirrel gun for many years. This particular shotgun comes with a professionally installed Cutts Compensator, three different screw on choke tubes and a wrench for changing the chokes. The choke installed in the pictures is a .725"ID "modified", the longer choke is a .690"ID LR#3 (similar to what is known as extra full nowadays) and the shortest choke is a .820"ID "spreader" (similar to a cylinder choke or no choke). There are many other choke sizes available on the market but these are the three I have and all that is included in this sale. The forearm has several impression marks and the "clear coat" has flaked on the butt stock around the receiver.
